.SS nvidia-mps
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl nvidia-mps [arguments]\f[R]
R551 (E11.M14): NVIDIA MPS controller.
Shares each non-MIG GPU across concurrent inference processes (pulse /
logic-engine / oracle-core + ad-hoc) without time-slicer context
switches.
Operator §1g: \[lq]Multi mode AI, multiple mode for the AI loadout\[rq].
.SS hugepages
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl hugepages [arguments]\f[R]
R552 (E11.M15): HugePages sizer.
Reserves 2MiB (or 1GiB) huge pages for inference engines (llama.cpp /
vllm / bitnet) to reduce TLB pressure.
Operator §1g: AVX-512 + 256GB RAM + ZMM ternary models \[em] all benefit
from huge-page-backed buffers.
.SS thp-mode
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl thp-mode [arguments]\f[R]
R553 (E11.M16): Transparent HugePage controller.
Orthogonal to R552 \[em] THP is the opportunistic path; reserved
hugepages are the static path.
inference policy = madvise+defer (no compaction stalls).
Operator §1g: predictable inference latency.
.SS irq-affinity
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl irq-affinity [arguments]\f[R]
R554 (E11.M17): IRQ affinity controller.
Moves all non-locked hardware-interrupt vectors onto a housekeeping CPU
set so the inference cores (pulse / logic-engine / oracle-core)
aren\[cq]t preempted by NIC RX, NVMe completion, USB poll, etc.
Operator §1g: peak-inference / sustained-burst latency hygiene.
.SS cpu-isolation
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl cpu-isolation [arguments]\f[R]
R557 (E11.M20): CPU isolation cmdline emitter.
Coordinated isolcpus/nohz_full/rcu_nocbs trifecta \[em] actually removes
the inference cores from the scheduler, the periodic tick, and RCU
callback processing.
Stronger than R554 IRQ pinning alone.
Never edits GRUB (operator sovereignty boundary); emits a fragment file
the operator merges on their own terms.
.SS nvidia-persistence
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl nvidia-persistence [arguments]\f[R]
R556 (E11.M19): NVIDIA persistence mode controller.
Without persistence ON, the driver tears down GPU state every time the
last CUDA context exits → next first-prompt pays \[ti]2s reinit latency.
Operator §1g: zero first-prompt thermal spike + inference-ready warmup.
.SS workload-knobs
.TP
\f[B]sovereign-osctl workload-knobs [arguments]\f[R]
R555 (E11.M18): atomic orchestrator of the R551-R554 inference-latency
primitives (MPS / hugepages / THP / IRQ).
Reads R338 active workload mode, maps it to a bundle preset, and fans
out to each underlying controller in one verb so the operator never has
to remember four commands per mode switch.
